meta.@content: Prototypes for HAnimBehavior node, which collects OrientationInterpolators for aggregate animation of an HAnim humanoid model, and HAnimBodyBehaviorChooser, which selects one body and enables/disables multiple aggregated behaviors.
Don Brutzman, Jeff Weekley, MV4205 Advanced X3D Authoring class, and Keith Victor
under development. should joint translations be exposed? upgrade to HAnim v2.2

ProtoDeclare.@appinfo: The HAnimBehavior node models a single humanoid behavior either for an entire body or simply parts of a body. It collects a TimeSensor clock with a single PositionInterpolator and multiple OrientationInterpolator nodes to provide a single humanoid behavior.

-children.#comment: shared common input for single TimeSensor animating all interpolators, since different Behaviors may have different cycleInterval durations
TODO: add other X3D 3.0 TimeSensor fields (pause etc.)
Not supported: animated translation of individual joints
pass in key/keyValue array pairs for single PositionInterpolator
pass in key/keyValue array pairs and expose named output for each OrientationInterpolator, joint by joint

field.@appinfo: Supported Level of Articulation (LOA) support needed by authored HAnimBehavior set of OrientationInterpolator values. Legal values 0 1 2 3.
is this behavior enabled?
how long do these interpolators take to execute?
whether or not this behavior loops (e.g. walking) or is single shot (e.g. shake hands).
when time now >= startTime isActive becomes true and TimeSensor becomes active
when stopTime becomes <= time now isActive becomes false and TimeSensor becomes inactive
when time now >= pauseTime isPaused becomes true and TimeSensor becomes paused
when resumeTime becomes <= time now isPaused becomes false and TimeSensor becomes inactive
cycleTime sends a time outputOnly at startTime and also at the beginning of each new cycle
isActive true/false events are sent when TimeSensor starts/stops running
isPaused true/false events are sent when TimeSensor is paused/resumed
current elapsed time since TimeSensor activated/running cumulative in seconds and not counting any paused time
continuously sends the absolute time (since January 1 1970)
fraction_changed continuously sends value in range [0 1] showing time progress in the current cycle.

-children.#comment: design alternative: move TimeSensor out of the prototype, instead expose set_fraction globally to all interpolators
note that other nodes following the first node in the ProtoBody are not rendered but remain active nevertheless

ProtoDeclare.@appinfo: The HAnimBodyBehaviorChooser node allows an author to select one of several HAnimHumanoid bodies and simultaneously apply multiple HAnimBehavior animations to the active body. Individual behaviors may be enabled or disabled at any time.

-children.#comment: TODO: supported Level of Articulation (LOA) might be adapted to more efficiently setup/teardown pertinent ROUTEs
accessType="inputOutput" avoided to maintain backwards compatilibility with VRML97 scripting constraints
shared common TimeSensor inputs for all BehaviorAnimation nodes, connected via ROUTEs
TODO: consider named accessors, e.g. enableBehaviorByName and disableBehaviorByName
TODO: consider addBody, removeBody, addBehavior, removeBehavior
TODO: consider startBehaviorByIndex, stopBehaviorByIndex, startBehaviorByName, stopBehaviorByName
